AN ACT relating to health care; requiring certain hospitals to establish staffing
committees for technical and service staff; establishing requirements
governing the staffing of certain health care facilities; requiring certain
hospitals to keep certain records relating to staffing; requiring certain
[health care facilities] hospitals to report [and publish] certain
information relating to staffing; prohibiting certain health care facilities
from taking certain retaliatory actions; providing for certain actions to
investigate and correct certain violations relating to staffing; providing
administrative penalties; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires certain hospitals in a county whose population is 100,000 or more
2 (currently Clark and Washoe Counties) to establish a staffing committee, which must consist,
3 in part, of certain nurses who are on the staff of the hospital. (NRS 449.242) Existing law
4 requires a hospital and certain other health care facilities in such counties to develop a
5 documented staffing plan which must include certain items, such as the number of nurses
6 required in each unit of the hospital and protocols for adequately staffing the hospital upon the
7 occurrence of certain events. (NRS 449.2421) If the health care facility is a hospital, existing
8 law requires the staffing committee established for the hospital to develop the staffing plan.
9 (NRS 442.242) Sections 5 and 6 of this bill require each hospital that is required to establish a
10 staffing committee for nurses to additionally establish a technical staffing committee and a
11 service staffing committee, respectively, to represent the technical and service workers of the
12 hospital. Sections 18-20 of this bill make conforming changes to refer to existing staffing
13 committees for nurses as “nursing staffing committees.” Sections 5, 6 and 18 require the
14 technical staffing committee, the service staffing committee and the nursing staffing
15 committee to collaborate to develop the documented staffing plan for the hospital. Section 19
16 requires a documented staffing plan to contain certain provisions relating to the adequate
17 staffing of technical and service workers. Section 23 of this bill requires a hospital that has
18 established a technical staffing committee and a service staffing committee to include the
19 members of those committees on the hospital’s committee on workplace safety, which

